[3] CHP: Avian Influenza Report
Date: Tue 2 Feb 2016
Source: Centre for Health Protection (CHP), Avian Influenza Report 12(5) [edited]
http://www.chp.gov.hk/files/pdf/2016_avian_influenza_report_vol12_wk05.pdf


Reporting period: 24-30 Jan 2016 (week 05)
------------------------------------------
Summary
-------
1. Since the previous issue of Avian Influenza Report (AIR), there were 2 new human cases of avian influenza A(H7N9), from Hunan (1) and Guangdong (1), as reported by mainland health authorities. Since March 2013 (as of 30 Jan 2016), there were a total of 702 human cases of avian influenza A(H7N9) reported globally. Since October 2015 (as of 30 Jan 2016), 25 cases have been recorded in mainland China.

2. Since the previous issue of AIR, there were no new human cases of avian influenza A(H5N6). Since 2013 (as of 30 Jan 2016), 10 human cases of avian influenza A(H5N6) have been detected globally and all occurred in Mainland China. These included 9 cases announced by the World Health Organization (WHO) and 1 case detected through routine surveillance and reported in the scientific literature.

3. There were no new human cases of avian influenza A(H5N1) reported by WHO. From 2011 to 2015, 32 to 145 confirmed human cases of avian influenza A(H5N1) were reported to WHO annually (according to onset date).

This week's highlights (Sources: WHO, National Health and Family Planning Commission (NHFPC), mainland health authorities, Centre for Health Protection (CHP), and World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE)).
